<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880729-0048 </DOCNO><HL> Financing Business: XL/DATACOMP Inc. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> XLDC </CO><IN> STK </IN><TEXT>   XL/DATACOMP Inc. said it began a public offering of 1.1 million shares at $24.50 a share. The company said 700,000 of the shares are being sold by certain stockholders and 400,000 by the Hinsdale, Ill., company, which currently has 6.9 million shares outstanding. A spokesman said the selling shareholders are company officers or directors. XL/Datacomp sells, distributes and services mid-range International Business Machines Corp. computer systems and peripheral equipment. It said proceeds from the shares sold by the company will be used for working capital and general corporate purposes, including spending to support expanded operations. The lead underwriter is Smith Barney, Harris Upham andamp; Co. </TEXT></DOC>